conditions vary greatly depending on location, experience and qualifications. free accommodation, provided by the institution, is common. generally this means an apartment of your own, though some tightfisted schools want teachers to share. most jobs pay for all or part of an annual trip home. teachers nearly always make enough to live well in china, though some have a problem in summer because many university or high school jobs pay for only the 10 months of the academic year. it is often possible to teach private lessons on the side - in fact your students or their parents may ask 